'''Bangladesh Sugarcrop Research Institute (BSRI)''' or BSRI,<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladesh sugar mills need more sugarcane|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/2016/01/19/11397|website=thefinancialexpress-bd.com|publisher=The Financial Express Online Version|accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref> is an autonomous national research institute that carries out research on [[Sugarcane]] and other related plants and is located in [[Ishwardi Upazila]], [[Pabna]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="lom">{{cite web|title=Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Bangladesh_Sugarcane_Research_Institute|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladesh experts see Inter-cropping with sugarcane brings more profit|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/2016/01/08/9752|website=thefinancialexpress-bd.com|publisher=The Financial Express Online Version|accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref> It falls under the ministry of agriculture.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brain drain dims achievements|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-255714|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=15 October 2016|date=1 November 2012}}</ref>
==History== In 1931 the Sugarcane Seedling Testing Station was established in Dhaka. It was changed to the Sugarcane Research Station on 1953 and placed under the Department of Agriculture. [[Bangladesh Sugar and Food Industries Corporation]] was placed in charge on the institute in 1973. In 1996 Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute was made an autonomous institute by an parliament act.<ref name="lom"></ref> It supports the cultivation of date palms and sugarcanes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jessore's signature date juice gets scarce|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/date-juice-road-be-history-575461|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=15 October 2016|date=21 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Power-sugar plant likely in the north|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-144406|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=15 October 2016|date=28 June 2010}}</ref> [[File:Main Office building of Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute.jpg|thumb|Main Office building of Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute]] [[File:Main Gate of Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute 01.jpg|thumb|Main Gate of Bangladesh Sugarcane Research Institute 01]] ==References== {{reflist|2}}
